Sure, here is a simple contract that fits your description:

```sol
// SPDX-License-Identifier

pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

contract MyContract {
    address private owner;

    constructor() {
        owner = msg.sender;
    }

    function withdraw() public {
        require(msg.sender == owner, "Only the owner can call this function.");
        payable(owner).transfer(address(this).balance);
    }
}
```

This contract does the following:
1. Sets the owner of the contract to the address that deploys it (in the constructor).
2. Provides a function `withdraw` that allows the owner to withdraw all Ether from the contract. The `require` statement ensures only the owner can call this function. The `payable(owner).transfer` line is what actually sends the Ether.
